title: [Vornavian Coast, Coastal Cliffs]
description: A line of lilac bushes grows along the path to the northeast, but only brief wafts of scent remain through the strong breezes blowing through.  Fireflies flitter about the lilacs, seeming to blink in and out of existence.  Purple and white flowers dot the bushes and lie on the path.

A line of lilac bushes grows along the path to the northeast, but only brief wafts of scent remain through the strong breezes blowing through.  Bees buzz about the lilacs, gathering nectar for a nearby hive.  Purple and white flowers dot the bushes and lie on the path.
